# Images are static crests/favicon and never change in place — cache 30 days to
# kill the per-page-view revalidation round-trips. CSS/JS are deliberately NOT
# long-cached here: filenames aren't fingerprinted, so they must keep
# revalidating (max-age=0) or deploys wouldn't reach users. Swap an image by
# renaming it if it ever needs to change before the cache expires.
/assets/img/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=2592000
